k to it<br />\n(2:06:08 PM) roddarn: Hi<br />\n(2:06:11 PM) jordannovak_: I’m Jordan Novak, partner at Novak Solutions LLC, www.novaksolutions.com<br />\n(2:06:14 PM) OF left the room (quit: Ping timeout: 246 seconds).<br />\n(2:06:28 PM) chrisdillon1: Hi, Chris Dillon @ wpmission.com<br />\n(2:06:29 PM) strangerstudios: (lol my kids started listening to Disney songs on Spotify and took over our account. That Weezer album is a little depressing anyway.)<br />\n(2:06:31 PM) NikV: Hi! I&#8217;m Nikhil. 15 year old WordPress developer. Nik.techvoltz.com<br />\n(2:06:33 PM) Ferris_TheOnline: Hi &#8211; RS Ferris &#8211; TheOnlieMagic.com<br />\n(2:06:47 PM) kriscargile: Kristopher Cargile, hipaa.com<br />\n(2:06:49 PM) strangerstudios: @Tubiz have some news RE the gateway stuff from 2.0<br />\n(2:06:53 PM) tubiz: Hi am Tunbosun a WordPress developer from Lagos, Nigeria. www.bosun.me<br />\n(2:06:54 PM) nocanvas: Hi I&#8217;m John, WP developer, used , created streaming video site Udaya.com with PMPro<br />\n(2:06:58 PM) sjolshagen: Hi. Thomas Sjolshagen &#8211; eighty20results.com/strongcubedfitness.com &#8211; using the plugin to manage gym memberships.<br />\n(2:06:58 PM) christianf3 [465b0de6@gateway/web/freenode/ip.70.91.13.230] entered the room.<br />\n(2:07:41 PM) strangerstudios: @nocanvas, noted RE JSON API<br />\n(2:07:45 PM) Erik1: Erik Bertrand here, basically a freelancer on the side, with a day job at Dyn (http://dyn.com) focusing on email delivery systems.  Been using PMPro for a single site so far since April or so, just launched at http://www.nhmade.com.  Relatively regular member forum participant, mostly asking, but trying to help here and there!<br />\n(2:08:13 PM) roddarn left the room (quit: Client Quit).<br />\n(2:08:14 PM) sjolshagen: Interested in v2 progress (specifically, multiple memberships per user as I&#8217;m thinking it&#8217;d be really interesting in the context of upsells etc.<br />\n(2:08:30 PM) sjolshagen: A fellow NH based developer